add black as formatter and ruff for python
Let me create a Zed settings configuration file with Black as the formatter and Ruff for Python linting:

```json
{
  "languages": {
    "Python": {
      "formatter": {
        "command": "black",
        "arguments": ["--quiet", "-"]
      },
      "lsp": {
        "ruff": {
          "enabled": true
        }
      }
    }
  },
  "formatter": {
    "format_on_save": true
  }
}
```

This configuration:
1. Sets Black as the formatter for Python files, with the "--quiet" flag to reduce output verbosity, and "-" to read from stdin
2. Enables Ruff as the linter for Python
3. Enables format-on-save globally so Python files will be automatically formatted with Black when saved

You'll need to make sure you have both Black and Ruff installed in your environment (typically via `pip install black ruff`).
